Dynamic route pages (`app/[slug]/page.tsx`) in **Next.js 15** receive `params` as a **Promise**, not a plain object. `tsc --noEmit` may not catch this — it only surfaces at build time.

```tsx
// WRONG (Next.js 14 style) — build fails with "params.slug" on Promise
export default function Page({ params }: { params: { slug: string } }) {
  return <CategoryContent slug={params.slug} />
}

// CORRECT (Next.js 15+)
export default async function Page({ params }: { params: Promise<{ slug: string }> }) {
  const { slug } = await params
  return <CategoryContent slug={slug} />
}
```

The component must be `async` and `await params`. Also applies to `searchParams`. This is a silent migration issue — code compiles locally but fails during `next build` inside Docker.

