## Product Deduplication Pattern

When products appear in multiple JSON arrays (featured, best sellers, new arrivals, full catalog), use **flags** on a single source array and derive sub-lists in components:

### In content/es.json
```json
{
  "home": {
    "productCatalog": {
      "products": [
        { "name": "Carpa 4 Personas", "category": "Camping", "featured": true, "isNew": true, ... },
        { "name": "Casco Integral", "category": "Motos", "featured": true, "isNew": false, ... }
      ]
    },
    "featuredProducts": { "title": "Destacados", "subtitle": "..." },
    "bestSellers": { "title": "Más vendidos", "subtitle": "..." },
    "newArrivals": { "title": "Nuevo en Stock", "subtitle": "..." }
  }
}
```

Keep the section headers (title/subtitle) but **delete the `products` arrays** from sub-sections.

### In components
```tsx
const products = h.productCatalog?.products || []
const newArrivals = products.filter((p: any) => p.isNew)
const featuredProducts = products.filter((p: any) => p.featured)
const bestSellers = products.filter((p: any) => p.featured).slice(0, 4)
```

This eliminated 17KB of duplicate data from es.json. The `productos.productCatalog.products` duplicate (identical to `home.productCatalog.products`) should also be removed — components under `/productos` can reference `home.productCatalog.products` directly.

### Legal Markdown Renderer (No dangerouslySetInnerHTML)

Use a shared `components/legal-renderer.tsx` that splits text by newlines and renders React elements:
- `# heading` → `<h1>`, `## heading` → `<h2>`, `- item` → `<li>`
- Inline `**bold**` parsed via regex into `<strong>` React elements (not innerHTML)
